This paper discusses the development of a testing toolkit for detecting unwarranted associations in data-driven applications. The paper focuses on the potential discriminatory effects of incorporating user data into algorithms, which suggests a focus on the ethical and social implications of computer science research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and data analytics, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the integration of the testing toolkit into a popular library for data analytics, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
